          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>268 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: R. 4; Qurʾānic Text: Q 14:21-23:55; 7 lines per page; Dimensions: 255 x 303mm; Script style: kūfī.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962) </ref>describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 27: "80 R. 4. Kur’andan bir bölüm. Parşömen. 303mm boy ve 255mm eninde 268 yaprak. Sahifede kalın kûfi ile 180mm uzunl.[uğunda] 7 satır. Tahmine göre VI (XII) asırda yazılmıştır. Bu cilt Kur’an’ın İbrahim (14) suresinin 21. ayetinden başlayıp Mü’minun (23) suresinin 55. ayetinin sonunda bitmektedir."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "80 R. 4. A part of the Qurʾān. Parchment. 268 leaves of 303 mm height and 255 mm width. The text area written in Kufic script [contains] 7 lines measuring 180 mm. Probably copied during 6th (12th) century. This part begins with Q 14:21 (Sūra Ibrāhīm) and ends at the end of Q 23:55 (Sūra al-Muʾminūn).”</p>
            </summary>
